      "text": "It seems sometimes as if men want very much to put an end to waiting on one an- other. There are many ways, for example, of making the serving of food in restaurants more or less automatic. One of the causes of the high price of food in restaurants is the use of waiters and wait- resses. One waitress can serve only a small number of people, if she has to go to and from the tables with trays. And fewer people than before are interested in doing this sort of work even when the",
